  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Wellbeing of Populations Affected by the Northern Ethiopia Crisis Is Strengthened through Camp Coordination and Camp Management (CCCM) Support to IDPs and Host Community</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of this action is to improve service provision in targeted sites in Ethiopia through coordination and information management, site planning and development, community participation and capacity building of key stakeholders. IOM&apos;s site management support (SMS) intervention includes all four pillars of SMS including site planning and development, coordination and information management, community participation and capacity building. The intervention aims to improve service provision in sites, coordination of response and increase the capacity of local stakeholders involved in camp coordination and camp management activities. COVID-19 mitigation will be mainstreamed into site management through risk communication &amp; community engagement, especially with and through community self-governance structures, site improvements that contribute to infection prevention and control, such as crowd control measures, decongestion and/or partitioning of communal living spaces.</narrative>
  </description>
